  3. Why the original version of the imbd dataset by Kaggle was taken down? https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/tmdb/tmdb-movie-metadata

    The original version of the IMDb dataset by Kaggle was taken down due to a legal claim by IMDb. The dataset contained information on movies and TV shows, including ratings and other data that was scraped from IMDbs website. IMDb claimed that the dataset violated their terms of service, which prohibit scraping and unauthorized use of their data. Kaggle removed the dataset from their platform in response to IMDbs claim.

  4. Comment on this websites web scrapping policy: https://help.imdb.com/article/imdb/general-information/can-i-use-imdb-data-in-my-software/G5JTRESSHJBBHTGX#

    The IMDb web scraping policy states that scraping IMDb data is strictly prohibited, except for personal and non-commercial use. This means that if you are scraping IMDb data for any commercial or public use, you must obtain a license from IMDb first.

  6. Is this data set tidy? Why?

    First check whether there is null or NA for each column

    colSums(is.na(df_ratings))
    ##        tconst averageRating      numVotes 
##             0             0             0

    Since there is no any records with null value. we can say it is tidy. Again we need to figure out the Tidy principle to say that the data is Tidy. According to the Tidy principle:

    ->Each variable must have its own column.

    ->Each observation must have its own row.

    ->Each value must have its own cell.

    The Data set follow the above rule so that we can say that the data set : df_ratings is Tidy

  7. What is difference between step 19 and step 20? Which one do you prefer? Why? Interpret the result of your choice.

    In the first step we create the new object that is grouped by genres then we filter the NA row and get the mean by using the summarize function. For the later we use the existing data frame df_rating and calculate the mean by using the pipe operates directly. I prefer second on as there is no need to create extra object to do the calculation we can directly calculate the mean from the existing data frame df_rating which is the join table of df_ratings and df_basic
